.TH "sock_alloc_file" 9 "sock_alloc_file" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sock_alloc_file \- Bind a &socket to a &file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct file *" sock_alloc_file
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "int flags "  ","
.BI "const char *dname "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket
.IP "flags" 12
file status flags
.IP "dname" 12
protocol name

Returns the \fIfile\fP bound with \fIsock\fP, implicitly storing it
in sock->file. If dname is NULL, sets to "".
On failure the return is a ERR pointer (see linux/err.h).
This function uses GFP_KERNEL internally.
